Ulmer SAR800
 

 

The coil unwinder SAR has been designed as a strain free cable feeder. The coil is driven by four synchronized drive rollers on the outside diameter of the coil flange.

The unwinder is controlled by and regulated by sag control DHS1000 or by dancer arm. The system guarantees that the product is feed to the processing machine without any pull in the opposite direction.

This concept eliminates the undesirable stretching of the insulation and coating of cables. The SAR has two centering cones, which allows processing of coils with damaged flanges.

Schleuniger PP3 (RIGHT HAND AVAILABLE)

 

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

Pneumatic Strip & Crimp Machine

 

Schleuniger's worldwide field-proven StripCrimp PP3 is a pneumatic machine for stripping and crimping wires from 32 to 16 AWG in one operation. Precision machine design and unique tooling make it the ideal solution for a wide range of applications. The compact benchtop machine is particularly famous for its thin wire processing capabilities, reliability and high quality output.

 

Highest Accuracy for Smallest Crimps

 

Precision stripping and gas tight crimps (certified with cross-section and test record if requested) guarantee maximum processing quality. The sensitive trigger sensor ensures accurate and repeatable wire placement. The cable's position remains unchanged during the entire stripping and crimping process, eliminating any damage or "brush effect" on the wire end strands. For smaller cross-sections as well as for thin-walled or extremely tough insulations special die-blades are available.

 

Choose Between Left or Right Feed

 

The StripCrimp PP3 is available in two versions: The StripCrimp PP3 L for side feed from the left or, alternatively, the StripCrimp PP3 R, designed for right side feed. Both versions can be used for rear feed terminals.

 

Quick Applicator Changeover? No Problem!

 

The applicators can be easily exchanged enabling very short change-over times, thus making the machine most suitable for small and medium production batches.

 

A particular Schleuniger speciality is the customer-specific tooling of applicators. Our crimping specialists have a long history of finding solutions for even the most difficult to process terminals. Customers from all over the world enjoy the benefits of working with Schleuniger high precision applicators. More than 20'000 sold applicators for more than 6'000 different types of terminals from all major terminal manufacturers are our best reference.

Schleuniger CO207 


The Schleuniger CO207 Cable stripping machine, is an electric table top model capable of stripping braided and stranded cables, wires as well as coaxial cables in diameters of up to 7mm over a length of up to 20mm in one multi-step (max 3 steps) operation and with high precision.  

Programming the individual stripping steps is a simple matter.  For each step you simply enter the desired strip length and diameter.  The CO207 lets you store and call up as many as 99 different pre-programmed sets of cable data.

The marking device MG10D is used for marking round material such as cables, cords, hoses and similar goods. A marking that is well visible and highly resistant is printed on the goods by pressing a coloured foil with heated embossing wheels or impression dies for a short time on the goods.

 

The marking plates will be produced according to the wishes of the customer. Even special markings are no problem. The impression bands can be engraved concavely with 27 or 40 symbols and a print size of 1,5 to 3 mm. Additionally, it is possible by using respective impression dies to produce a round marking.

 

The material delivery and the printing are done by a SM15 series cutting machine or a similar cutting machine or cable stripper. Temperature and pressing time are regulated continuously.

HotStamp 4140  

 

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

Concept

 
The Schleuniger model HotStamp 4140 is designed for the economical and high qual-ity marking of wires and tubes. The combination of characters and character size can be selected freely within the specific range. The Hot-Stamp Marking process is suit-able for marking thermoplastic materials.
 
 
 
Function
 
During the process the preheated character wheels imprint the precision-engraved characters by pressing the pigmented marking foil into the selected material. The concave form of the characters is exactly matched to the diameter of the processed material. The precise adjusting options for the stamping pressure and time and the marking temperature allow to recall every result.
Special Features
 
􀂃 Schleuniger Hot Stamp Marking Systems are designed for usage with Schleuni-ger cut and strip equipment. The characters of the character wheel can be changed quickly with the index system and contribute therefore to the high eco-nomic efficiency.
􀂃 Without having to change the character wheels it is possible to realize up to 25-digit markings in alpha-numeric characters.
􀂃 For the processing of flat materials (tubes, shrink down tubes) a die bracket for retaining single embossing dies is offered instead of the character wheel with concave engraved characters.

Schleuniger HotStamp 4500  

 

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

 

The HotStamp 4500 performs end marking of wire and cable up to 15 mm (0.59”) O.D on a variety of insulation types including PVC, Teflon, Tefzel, Cross-linked, SXL and GXL. Its wide carriage enables this compact unit to mark each end of the wire and cable with a different alphanumeric string up to 16 characters long.
 
Since both leading and trailing end marks are applied at the same time, it can also perform double continuous marking at set intervals for greater production rates. The HotStamp 4500 easily interfaces with any Schleuniger cut & strip machine or the OC 3950 cutter. An optional foot-pedal is also available for stand-alone operation.
 
Features:

  •  Stroke adjustment to ensure maximum production rate based on wire size
  •  Large selection of character sizes and foils
  •  Standard V-block wire guide allows marking on cable up to 15 mm (0.59”) O.D.

  •  Closed loop integral temperature controller

Schleuniger CS5300

 Click to view the Product Brochure
 

Programmable Coaxial Cable Stripping Machine

The CoaxStrip 5300 is a semi-automatic, programmable multi-step stripping machine for coaxial, triaxial, multi-conductor cable and single conductor wire. This benchtop unit can easily process coaxial and triaxial cables up to 7 mm (0.276') outer diameter and strips lengths up to 30 mm (1.18").

State-of-the-art electronics, a user-friendly graphic display, included Iguana PC Software and precision mechanics guarantee repeatable, unmatched Schleuniger stripping quality. With a sample programming library and 1000 program memory, this machine is ideal for low volume, quick change-over applications as well as high volume production runs, giving the best possible flexibility and productivity to your production methods. 

A Worthy Successor to the MP 257

The CoaxStrip 5300 is the successor to the legendary MP 257 coaxial cable stripping machine, that set the industry standard in high quality stripping ever since its market introduction more than 20 years ago.

Unmatched Precision

The unique stripping head design combines universal stripping blades with a universal centering system. This allows the CoaxStrip 5300 to process the entire range of cable types and diameters with no no blade change whatsoever. The patented stripping head is precision-built to guarantee unparalleled stripping quality and repeatable results.

High Performance & User-Friendliness

Short cycle times and wire list processing ensure high performance and will yield you a quick return on investment. To guarantee short operator training times, the CoaxStrip 5300 can be programmed intuitively with a Graphical User Interface (GUI).

Its high-resolution monochrome display allows the user to view a schematic diagram of the cable end, complete with programmed dimensions.

products_name: Schleuniger SR1000 Semi Rigid Coax Machine
products_description:
Schleuniger SR1000

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

Programmable Stripping Machine for Semi-Rigid Coaxial Cables

The SemiRigid 1000 is specifically designed to strip semi-rigid coaxial cable up to 4.5 mm (0.177") outer diameter (O.D.) at a maximum stripping length of 35 mm (1.37''). It combines all necessary stripping and pointing functions in one programmable unit.

 

The machine uses one set of cutting blades to strip and remove the outer conductor and dielectric, leaving the center conductor exposed at the programmed length and diameter setting. If a two-step strip is needed, a second set of blades incises the outer jacket at the required length and the jacket can be removed with a special stripping tool. If pointing is desired, a third set of blades points the center conductor at the desired angle to the programmed pointing diameter.

products_description:
Schleuniger CS9200

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

Automatic Cut & Strip Machine for Micro-Coaxial Cable

The CompactStrip 9200 MX processes extremely short micro coaxial cables and most wire and cable types up to 3.5 mm (0.14") O.D. with pull-off lengths up to 8 mm (0.31"). This machine is specifically designed to process precision micro coaxial cables with uncompromising production quality and an unmatched throughput rate.

Highest Precision for Smallest Cables

Very short wires can be processed without moving the insulation of the conductor which results in highly accurate total and stripping lengths.

With its unique rotary incision unit (MX type), the CompactStrip 9200 MX advances to a state of unprecedented precision processing of smallest coaxial and micro coaxial cables.

The patented rotary incision head design combines rotary incision blades with a universal centering system. Precision-built parts and assembly guarantee unparalleled stripping quality and repeatable results wherever highest quality is required.

 

Automatic Inline Cable Processing

There are various accessories available for the CompactStrip 9200 MX. Contact your local Schleuniger sales & service representative for a recommendation on the pre- and post-processing equipment best suited for your production needs.

Schleuniger CC1300 

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

 

The Cable Coiler 1300 is a stand-alone, fully synchronized high performance cable coiler for cut and strip machines. It coils all types of round cable with a maximum outer diameter of 12 mm (0.47") in high quality. Coiling diameters from 110 – 230 mm (4.33" - 9.06") and coil weights up to 10 kg (22.05 lb) allow for flexible production.
 
High Performance - Short Changeover Times
 
This automatic dual pan coiling machine achieves very high output rates thanks to a combination of high coiling speed, fast switching between coiling pans, and movements that are perfectly synchronized with the transport units of the upstream cut & strip machine. The all-electric Cable Coiler 1300 is virtually maintenance-free.
 
The alternating coiling process with a dual pan system eliminates unproductive waiting times. While the operator is unloading a completed coil from the first coiling pan, the next coil is already produced on the second pan. An anti-slip surface on the inside of the coiling pans in conjunction with coiling pins assure a controlled coiling process.
 
Programming the CableCoiler 1300 is fast and simple with an intuitive touch screen user interface. Thanks to only a few configuration settings, changeover time between different jobs is minimized. This way, handling even very small batch sizes can be productive.

Schleuniger CC500

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

The CableCoiler 500 is a light-weight, economical single pan coiling machine used to coil wire or cable weighing up to 4 kg (8.8 lbs.).

It is designed to interface with Schleuniger automatic cutting and stripping machines. Thanks to its flexibility, ease of use and ergonomic design, the CableCoiler 500 is the perfect solution to improve the production rate and efficiency of your wire or cable processing line.

 

As the wire or cable exits the cutting and stripping machine, it passes through a guide tube and into the CableCoiler 500 coiling pan. The coiling pan speed is synchronized with the speed of the exiting wire or cable, making a uniform sized coil. The diameter of the coil can be changed easily. Once the wire stops feeding and the coiling pan stops, the operator manually unloads the wire or cable and initiates another cycle on the cutting and stripping machine.

Automatic Coiling Machine

The Schleuniger CableCoiler 1000 is a dual-pan coiling machine for use with all standard cable products ranging from simple flexible cables (2 mm / 0.078" O.D.) to heavy, stiff control cables (12 mm / 0.47" O.D.). Bi-directional processing for cables with long-stripped ends.

The CAN interface to the upstream cut or cut & strip machine ensures both machines are completely synchronized, thus reducing the risk of damage to even the most delicate material, e.g. fiber optic cables.

After only a few quick programming steps, the cable is fed by the upstream cut or cut & strip machine through a guide tube into one of the coiling pans. Each coiling pan has a skid-resistant coating on the inner surface to assist the coiling process. When the end of the cable is detected, a mechanical switch redirects the next cable into the alternate guide tube that leads to the second coiling pan. The previously coiled cable can now be removed from the first pan. This process repeats throughout the entire production cycle.

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

Automatic Coiling Machine

Heavy-duty single pan coiling system for in-line or stand-alone coiling of wire, cable or tubing. Coils cables up to an inner diameter of 300 mm (13") and handles coils weighing up to 40 kg (88 lbs.). It features a rotary design with moveable pins to adjust for different coiling diameters. Several parameters can be programmed.

Easy Handling of Heavy Coils

Another unique feature of this design is the easy unloading scheme, using retracting pins and an automatic safety cover lift. The machine is very versatile and can function in one of two different operating modes:

  • Coil only - for efficient offline coiling of precut materials
  • Auto coil - as an integrated post-processing accessory for use with cut & strip machines.

As the turntable rotates, the material is coiled around the inner pins. When the coiling is complete, turning stops and the safety cover opens automatically. The pins retract downwards until they are flush with the turntable so the operator can easily remove the coiled material.

Schleuniger Cable Coiler 2000

Automatic Coiling Machine

The CableCoiler 2000 is a high demand cable coiling system. It enables fully automatic coiling of small, tension-sensitive cables and wires with diameters of 2 mm (0.079"), e.g. Glass Optical Fibers as well as heavy cables up to 10 mm (0.39") in diameter. Optional guides enable the processing of cables with diameters ranging between ~ 0.7 mm (0.028") - 14 mm (0.55").

Thanks to the configuration with two alternating turntables, the operator can unload a finished coil from the first turntable while the machine is coiling the next wire or cable on the second one.

High-Quality Coils & Economical Processing

The cable end can be precisely positioned and clamped. For variable coiling heights and high-quality coils, the level winding feature can be activated on demand. Synchronized, highly dynamic feeding and coiling processes between the cable processing machine and the CableCoiler 2000 ensure minimal tension forces and high-quality coils.

The coiling parameters are provided by the Schleuniger cut & strip machine which enables short changeover times and economical processing even when running small batches

Schleuniger WS500

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

Passive Stacking Machine

 

The Wire Stacker 500 is a passive wire stacking system with guide channel and collecting tray. It handles cable lengths up to 1.5 m (5 ft) and wires as small as 0.34 mm2 (AWG 22).

After processing of each wire, the cut & strip machine sends a signal to the stacker initiating the dropping of the wire from the guide channel into the collecting tray. All programming such as total and batch quantities is done on the cut & strip machine.

The Wire Stacker 500 is the ideal low-cost solution for post-processing of both short and long cables. It allows unattended operation. This wire stacker is optimized for use with Schleuniger cutting and cut & strip machines, thus permitting trouble-free and efficient processing.

 

Give Your Processing Line the Edge!

 

In order to maintain the quality of a carefully processed cable, it is highly recommended to use post-processing equipment such as a wire stacking or a cable coiling machine.

Active Stacking Machine

 

The Wire Stacker 3100 is a modular high-performance wire stacker for the precise, axial stacking of cables. The system consists of either a base element of 2.5 m (8.2 ft) or a base element with an extrension to 5 m (16.4 ft). The modules can be cascaded in combination according to required cable lengths. Built-in, synchronized driven transport belts allow to stack cables carefully and safely without cable jam even for very flexible cables.

Excelling Performance in Precise Stacking

 

The Wire Stacker 3100 excels with exceptional performance and flexibility making it an important element within an efficient and precise cable processing line.

 

The Wire Stacker 3100 base and extension modules are controlled by an upstream cable processing machine via CAN-Bus. This allows the Wire Stacker 3100 to operate as a fully integrated part of a processing line. Apart from transporting the cable, the 45° tilted transport belt also provides for optimum guiding and a secured ejection of the cable.

 

Give Your Processing Line the Edge!

 

In order to maintain the quality of a carefully processed cable, it is highly recommended to use post-processing equipment such as a wire stacking or a cable coiling machine.

Schleuniger PT26

 Click to view the Product Guide

 

Schleuniger's PullTester 26 is a dual-range, motorized benchtop device designed to measure pull forces of wire crimp connections as well as ultrasonic metal welding connections on a wider range of wire than single-range pull test devices. The PullTester 26 is specially suited for quality assurance in a production environment.

 

The measured values are indispensable parameters for quality control and assurance (e.g. IEC 60352-2 standard). Certain standards require measuring at the maximum measured force (destructive test). In addition to the base model PullTester 25, the PullTester 26 can also perform non-destructive tests (hold to a specified force). It also features an additional pulling mode where the wire is pulled until the required target value is reached, then hold in this position and as a further step then pulled until the crimped connection breaks. 
 

Two Individual Displays

 

Two individual displays show all necessary data: Measured values are indicated in the upper display and operators are automatically prompted to save them after each job. All job settings (e.g. target value) are permanently visible during operation in the lower LCD display. Its four lines make menu navigation easier than ever. Terminal names are clearly stated simplifying the choice of a measuring sequence.

Measure Highest Accuracy

 

The versatile PullTester 26 has two measuring ranges which are individually calibrated enabling the use if its 500 N (110 lb.) scale for small wires, while easily switching to its 1000 N (220 lb.) scale for larger wires. This dual-range capability ensures the highest accuracy for the widest range of applications.

 

The standard 12 position terminal holder accommodates a wide variety of terminals to suit most applications, however, a variety of terminal holders are available upon request.

 

Hand actuated or pneumatic pull test devices can give inconsistent data depending on the operator or pull rate. The IEC standard specifies that a pull tester measures with a consistent pull rate. The Schleuniger PullTester 26 is equipped with a controlled speed motor, ensuring consistent pull rates throughout the measuring range wihich means repeatable and accurate data. Pull forces can be measured in pounds, Newton or kilopounds.

 

Integrate The PullTester 26 Into Your Network

 

The PullTester 26 can be integrated into a quality network which ties in crimp height, pull test and crimp force data. Pull test data can be stored in the PullTester 26 for future reference or to be downloaded for statistical evaluation. Curve analysis and statistics can also be evaluated via the optional WinCrimp PC software.

Schleuniger PT20

The PullTester 20 is an economical motorized benchtop device for measuring pull forces of crimp connections as well as ultrasonic metal welding connections.

 

The measured values are indispensible parameters for quality control and assurance such as the IEC 60 352-2 standard. This standard requires measuring with a consistent pulling rate at the maximum measured force (destructive test).

 

Measure Highest Accuracy

Hand actuated or pneumatic pull test devices can give inconsistent data depending on the operator pull rate. The IEC standard specifies that a pull tester measures with a consistent pull rate. The Schleuniger PullTester 20 is equipped with a controlled speed motor, ensuring consistent pull rates throughout the measuring range which means repeatable and accurate data.

 

All PullTester 20 models offer selectable pull speeds: PullTester 20-25 with 25 or 50 mm/min (0.98" or 1.97"/min) and PullTester 20-50 as well as PullTester 20-TCP with 50 or 100 mm/min (1.97" or 3.94"/min). Pull forces can be measured in pounds, Newton or kilopounds.

Analysis & Network Integration

Curve analysis and statistics can be done via the optional WinCrimp PC software. With WinCrimp you can also set up an entire crimp quality assurance network, e.g. by networking the PullTester 20 with a StripCrimp 750 CFM and a CHME crimp height measuring device.

 

 

The PullTester 20 is specially designed for use with all Schleuniger fully automatic swivel arm crimping machines of the CrimpCenter series. Curve analysis and statistics are then done directly in the CrimpCenter machine software EASY.

Schleuniger StripCrimp LCP

 

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

 

The StripCrimp LPC is a semi-automatic benchtop machine for processing turned loose piece terminals (closed barrel) with a cross section range from 0.14 – 2.5 mm² (AWG 26 – 14). Key component is a highly flexible feeding module that first sorts and separates terminals with an integrated drum / track system and subsequently brings them into the correct crimping position.

 

To ensure highest accuracy and repeatability, manually inserted wires are held in position by an integrated gripper after the sensor has been triggered. Thanks to its compact design, the StripCrimp LPC is ideally suited for processing the inner conductors of multi-conductor cables – even with short break-out lengths below 25 mm (0.98").

 

Operating the StripCrimp LPC is simple with logical menu structures and an ergonomically designed PAWOPILOT handheld device. Thanks to its excellent accessibility from all sides (safety cover lifts up completely), change-overs to other terminals using change-over kits, exchange of the feeding module, or blade changes are done quickly and comfortably. Modular change-over kits reduce machine downtime to a minimum and allow flexible processing of different terminal sizes and geometries (male / female).

 

The StripCrimp LPC can be equipped with three exchangeable feeding modules for different terminal feeding types:

 

Next to common MIL-standard crimp applicators, Schleuniger offers an innovative alternative: the 4 pin – 8-point crimp of the PAWO PrismaCrimper with integrated step-less crimp depth adjustment and the possibility of integrating crimp force monitoring.

 

With its integrated stripping unit, standard zero cut function, programmable processing sequences and exchangeable feeding modules for all terminal feeding types, the StripCrimp LPC is used in semi-automatic production environments where flexibility and high precision according to MIL standard are essential.

 

High-precision mechanics combined with proven sorting & feeding technology, integrated process monitoring, short cycle times, and simple operation make the StripCrimp LPC a reliable solution tailored to individual production requirements for flexible high-precision processing of loose piece terminals.

 

The StripCrimp LPC is also available as benchtop crimping machine (UniCrimp LPC B) and automatic crimping station for fully automatic crimping machines (UniCrimp LPC A).

Schleuniger Seal Crimp 210 B

 

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

 

The SealCrimp 210 B is a highly flexible benchtop machine for stripping, sealing, and crimping a great variety of different wire sizes up to 2.5 mm². The machine can process a great variety of crimp terminals and seal types including mini seals and hard-shell seals. Due to its modular design it can also be used as a stripper, stripper-crimper, or a crimping machine.

 

Setup of processing parameters such as stripping length, incision depth and seal position is simple and precise. High-quality components and precision-built machine design guarantee reliable processes and high repeatability at short cycle times – and provide for a long machine life time.

 

The machine features integrated quality assurance and comes standard with crimp force monitoring, zero-cut function, carrier strip cutter and bad piece cutter.

 

Fast & Flexible

 

Seal-kits for almost all types of seals, exchangeable stripping cassettes which can be equipped with standard V-blades or die blades and a quick-change applicator base plate assure a simple and quick change-over between different applications. Unproductive machine downtime is therefore reduced to a minimum.

 

The SealCrimp 210 B accepts standard crimp applicators such as the Schleuniger Uni-A. All change-over kits are fully compatible with Schleuniger sealing stations used on fully automatic crimping machines.

 

Simple Operation

 

Operating the SealCrimp 210 B is simple with a user-friendly multi-lingual handheld device with clearly structured user interface that also displays all crimp force monitoring results during operation. The navigation via menu and programmable buttons allows a fast and direct access. All parameters can be set directly, incl. press speed, vibrator and timer. The access is protected with passwords or key cards (option) for various user levels.

 

Integrated Quality Assurance

 

Crimp force monitoring and additional quality assurance functions are all standard with the SealCrimp 210 B. If a faulty crimp is detected by the integrated crimp force monitoring, the bad piece cutter automatically destroys the wire immediately. All rejected parts are collected separately from other waste such as insulation pieces or cut carrier strips. Optionally, the presence of a seal prior to each seal assembly can be monitored to prevent scrap production (SealCheck function).

Schleuniger UniCrimp LPC B

 

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

The UniCrimp LPC B is a semi-automatic benchtop machine for processing turned loose piece terminals (closed barrel) with a cross section range from 0.14 – 4 mm² (AWG 26 – 12).

 

A combined drum / track system feeds, sorts and separates the loose piece terminals and subsequently brings them into the correct crimping position. Modular change-over kits reduce machine downtime to a minimum and allow flexible processing of different terminal sizes and geometries (male / female).

 

Depending on the terminal feeding type, the UniCrimp LPC B is available in 3 versions:

 

Next to common MIL-standard crimp applicators, Schleuniger offers an innovative alternative: the 4 pin – 8-point crimp of the PAWO PrismaCrimper with integrated step-less crimp depth adjustment and the possibility of integrating crimp force monitoring.

 

High-precision mechanics combined with proven sorting & feeding technology, integrated process monitoring, short cycle times, and simple operation make the UniCrimp LPC B a reliable solution tailored to individual production requirements for flexible high-precision processing of loose piece terminals.

 

The UniCrimp LPC B is also available as automatic crimping station for fully automatic crimping machines (UniCrimp LPC A) and as stripper-crimper (StripCrimp LPC).

Schleuniger PT25 - Pull Force Testing Device

 Click to view the Product Brochure

Pull Force Testing Device

The PullTester 25 is a dual-range, motorized benchtop device for measuring pull forces of crimp connections as well as ultrasonic metal welding connections on a broader range of wires than single-range pull test devices.

The measured values are indispensible parameters for quality control and assurance (e.g. IEC 60352-2 standard). Certain standards require measuring at the maximum measured force (destructive test).

The versatile PullTester 25 has two measuring ranges which are individually calibrated enabling the use of its 500 N (110 lb.) scale for small wires, while easily switching to its 1000 N (220 lb.) scale for larger wires. This dual-range capability ensures the highest accuracy for the widest range of applications.

The standard 12 position terminal holder accommodates a wide variety of terminals to suit most applications, however, a variety of terminal holders are available upon request.

Measure Highest Accuracy

Hand actuated or pneumatic pull test devices can give inconsistent data depending on the operator pull rate. The IEC standard specifies that a pulltester measures with a consistent pull rate. The Schleuniger PullTester 25 is equipped with a controlled speed motor, ensuring consistent pull rates throughout the measuring range which means repeatable and accurate data. Pull forces can be measured in pounds, Newton or kilopounds.

Analysis & Network Integration

Curve analysis and statistics can be done via the optional WinCrimp PC software. With WinCrimp you can also form an entire crimp quality assurance network, i.e. by networking the PullTester 25 with a StripCrimp 750 CFM and a CHME crimp height measuring device.

The PullTester 25 can also be integrated with all Schleuniger fully automatic swivel arm crimping machines of the CrimpCenter series. Curve analysis and statistics are then done directly in the CrimpCenter machine software EASY.

The cutting machines of the series SMH cut materials with a width of 40mm max. and a height of 30mm max..

Pneumatic opening and closing of the belt feed
Cutting Unit

Schleuniger FO7010
 Click to view the Product Brochure



Kevlar Cutting Machine

The low-cost FibreOptic 7010 cuts and removes the Kevlar material of fiber optic cables with complete accuracy to a remaining length between 3 and 60 mm (0.12 and 2.36").

An efficient vacuum system, activated by means of a foot pedal, separates the Kevlar material from the optical conductor of the cable. The Kevlar is then positioned between the cutting head and anvil. The number of cutting strokes can be adapted to the thickness of the material by means of operating the foot pedal several times.

This extremely light benchtop machine is easy to operate and guarantees repeatable results and a precise cutting performance.

The FibreOptic 7010 is best deployed in a work cell with other Schleuniger machines for Glass Optical Fiber (GOF) processing:

  • OmniCut 3950: cutting to length

  • UniStrip 2545: the jacket is stripped partially and can easily be removed by hand

  • FiberOptic 7010: severing and removal of the Kevlar strands

  • FiberStrip 7030 or FiberStrip 7035: stripping of the buffer and / or coating


Alternatively, all of the operations except for cutting to length can also be performed automatically with the FiberOptic 7045.

Schleuniger FS7035

The extremely light FiberStrip 7035 was specifically designed for use in a production environment or during the installation of cable systems with fiber ribbons with 2 up to 18 fibers. The FiberStrip 7035 handles strip lengths up to 35 mm (1.4").

This handy machine serves as an ideal companion to cleaving and splicing devices for standard and high strength applications. The FiberStrip 7035 is the first stripper on the market with a motorized stripping stroke allowing for repeatable processes to be documented and completely eliminating operator variability.

Acceleration and speed are also controlled by the stripping stroke ensuring consistent results. The unit additionally features a closed loop temperature control that ensures repeatable stripping quality. The FiberStrip 7035 accepts most common fusion splicer fiber holders. Only clamping and removal of the fiber ribbon are done manually, permitting simple and economical processing.

The Fiber Strip 7035 simply is the best way to strip fiber ribbon. The heaters soften the fiber coatings, making them easier to strip. Precision mechanics in a small package offer high, repeatable stripping quality. This economical stripping machine is also equipped with a status LED for better control as well as a stand-by function.

Solder Station 951A

The 951 Solder Station is a temperature controlled digital unit and includes the station, iron and stand.

The unit is designed for  bench mounting and has a temperature range of 200 to 4 50° F  which is selected using the keypad .  The display will show the temperature and the heater LED will light up to indicate the preset temperature is ready.

 

The 3 digi display , depending on the selected display mode, will show one of the following:

 

Normal mode - tip temperature 

Input value 

Display temperature unit (ºC or ºF) 

Error code

 

The Solder Station also has a temperature compensation facility, for example if the setting is 400ºF but the temperature of the tip is 410ºF, the delta is -10ºF. By using the keypad, it is then a simple process to select  the compensation setting.

 

For safety, this unit also has a power saving mode which is able to be adjusted to the desired time, is RoHS compliant and ESD safe.

The JacketStrip 8310 axially and radially slits the insulation of out-of-round and multi-conductor cables from 2.5 - 25 mm (0.1" - 1'') O.D. and up to 500 mm (19.7") in stripping length without any damage to the inner conductors or shielding.

Pneumatic Stripping Machine

The UniStrip 2500 is a pneumatic wire and cable stripping machine and the perfect solution for stripping discrete wires and small multi-conductor cables up to 6 mm (0.24") O.D..

The compact machine strips lengths up to 30 mm (1.18") and comes standard with V-blades, the optimum solution for any ordinary stripping of stranded wire with no blade changeover necessary.

A Simple Solution for Versatile Cable Processing

Through the use of special blades, the range of applications can be expanded to include flat ribbon cable, double-stranded wire, thin multi-stranded wire or demanding (tough, delicate, thin) isolations. The adjustable wayback prevents the conductor from being damaged during the stripping process.

UniStrip 2500 machines prove themselves each day in countless industrial plants around the world. Extremely short cycle times and infinite settings for conductor diameters, stripping and pull-off lengths boost productivity immensely when building harnesses or other quick-change wire stripping applications.

Operating the US 2500 is extremely simple. After insertion, the cable makes contact with the sensor, which then actuates the visually controllable stripping process. Alternatively a foot pedal is available as an option.

Schleuniger CC36 Crimp Center

 Click to view the Product Brochure
 

The Schleuniger 3-Series with the CrimpCenter 36 is an economical alternative to the proven High Performance 6-Series of fully automatic crimping machines. Dynamic and powerful servo drives combined with an intelligent control system provide high production rates to meet the most demanding production schedules.

Equipped with reliable high precision technology, the CrimpCenter 36 features a compact modular design offering space for up to 6 processing stations without compromising the high Schleuniger quality standards of the 6-Series. Various configuration possibilities allow for a variety of applications to be processed with cross sections from 0.13 to 4 mm² (AWG 26 - AWG 12). An optimal combination of proven state-of-the-art components results in outstanding production rates.

Various configuration possibilities on the same base plate provide for great flexibility allowing specific applications or special solutions with up to 3 crimping stations.

The crimping station UniCrimp 220 A with integrated crimp force monitoring CFM 20 and optional programmable crimp height adjustment has been specifically designed to maximize the efficiency of the 3-Series. The integrated concept of quality assurance during production includes pull force measuring, splice detection and micrograph analysis.

To minimize machine downtime, the CrimpCenter 36 can be equipped with Schleuniger's innovative ToolingShuttle System (TSS). The ToolingShuttle 30 combines crimp applicator, terminal reel and paper winder in one mobile unit to minimize applicator and terminal change-over time.

A synchronized ethernet powerlink ensures fast and continuous communication between software and the 5 servo drives. The established EASY software of the 6-Series with touch screen interface and icon-based menus is also implemented in the CrimpCenter 3-Series making this model just as flexible and user-friendly.

Machine Layout & Processing Stations

The CrimpCenter 36 can be fitted with up to 6 processing stations for crimping, applying weather seals and twisting & tinning conductor end strands.

Thanks to the adaptable base plate and the flexible software concept, integration of various processes is possible. In below shown sample configurations there are different applications possible without changing the basic machine layout

Schleuniger Wire Twist 500 (WT500)

 Click to view the Product Brochure
 

 

The WireTwist 500 is a programmable bench top twisting machine for twisting multiple single wires from 0.25 mm² - 2.5 mm² (23 - 13 AWG). It accepts stripped or crimped wires either with or without seals. Twisting single wires gives the twisted wires a higher stability for easier wire routing and improved protection against electromagnetic interference.

The WireTwist 500 consists of an electrically driven power unit and a compact holding unit. It twists wires of approximately 330 mm (13") - 2'000 mm (79"). Longer wires up to 5'000 mm (197") can also be twisted using a wire guide between the units. The final twisted wire length depends on the wire diameter and the number of required twists.

Change-over to different wire lengths and wire diameters is done easily and quickly. Custom adapters (e.g. for wires with housing) or other special applications can be made according to customer specifications.

Programming and operation are accomplished on the clearly structured key pad and display. Order parameters such as revolution speed and number or revolutions (forward and reverse) can be saved to and loaded from the internal memory. This allows processing of different applications with high repeatability and consistent quality without compromising flexibility. For batch and total pieces a counter is integrated.

Schleuniger Wire Twist 1000 (WT1000)

 Click to view the Product Brochure
 

The Wire Twist 1000 is a programmable twisting machine for twisting 2 or more single conductor wires from 0.25 mm² - 2.5 mm² (23 - 13 AWG). It accepts stripped or crimped wires either with or without seals. Twisting single wires gives the twisted wires a higher stability for easier wire routing and improved protection against electromagnetic interference.


The final twisted wire length depends on the wire diameter and the number of twists required. The minimum untwisted wire length is approximately 315 mm (12.4”) and approximately 4'000 mm (157’’) maximum length. For processing wires up to 10 m (394’’), an optional extension unit is available (wire samples recommended).

Programming the Wire Twist 1000 is simple. A clearly structured display allows forward and reverse twist capability with adjustable twisting speed. Parameters can be saved and loaded from the internal memory. This allows processing of different applications with high repeatability without compromising flexibility.

The Wire Twist 1000 additionally features quick change-overs for different lengths and wire diameters, an integrated counter for batch and total pieces as well as additional memory to store order parameters. An integrated contact-free lenght-measuring system checks the wire length before and after twisting. Special adapters (e.g. for wires with terminal housings) or other special applications can be made according to customer specifications.

products_name: Schleuniger PP3 Stripping and Crimping Machine
products_description:
Schleuniger PP3

 

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

Pneumatic Strip & Crimp Machine

 

Schleuniger's worldwide field-proven StripCrimp PP3 is a pneumatic machine for stripping and crimping wires from 32 to 16 AWG in one operation. Precision machine design and unique tooling make it the ideal solution for a wide range of applications. The compact benchtop machine is particularly famous for its thin wire processing capabilities, reliability and high quality output.

 

Highest Accuracy for Smallest Crimps

 

Precision stripping and gas tight crimps (certified with cross-section and test record if requested) guarantee maximum processing quality. The sensitive trigger sensor ensures accurate and repeatable wire placement. The cable's position remains unchanged during the entire stripping and crimping process, eliminating any damage or "brush effect" on the wire end strands. For smaller cross-sections as well as for thin-walled or extremely tough insulations special die-blades are available.

 

Choose Between Left or Right Feed

 

The StripCrimp PP3 is available in two versions: The StripCrimp PP3 L for side feed from the left or, alternatively, the StripCrimp PP3 R, designed for right side feed. Both versions can be used for rear feed terminals.

 

Quick Applicator Changeover? No Problem!

 

The applicators can be easily exchanged enabling very short change-over times, thus making the machine most suitable for small and medium production batches.

 

A particular Schleuniger speciality is the customer-specific tooling of applicators. Our crimping specialists have a long history of finding solutions for even the most difficult to process terminals. Customers from all over the world enjoy the benefits of working with Schleuniger high precision applicators. More than 20'000 sold applicators for more than 6'000 different types of terminals from all major terminal manufacturers are our best reference.

Automatic Cut & Strip Machine with Rotary Incision Unit

The PowerStrip 9500 RS processes wires up to 12 mm (0.47") in diameter with pull-off lengths up to 40 mm (1.57"). Specifically designed for precision processing of coaxial cables, the PowerStrip 9500 RS also processes various other wires and cables - all with highest production quality and an unmatched throughput rate.

Due to the presence of the rotary incision unit in combination with the patented Schleuniger indexing cutter head, the PowerStrip 9500 RS advances to a state of unprecedented versatility and processes virtually all coaxial cable types and many other cables from 0.03 - 25 mm² (AWG 4 - 32).

 

Our Technology & Your Benefits

The unique rotary incision head design combines rotary incision blades with a universal centering system. As a result, blade changes on the incision head are not required, enabling even faster cable processing and short changeover times. Precision-built parts guarantee highest quality and repeatability.

The multiple blade system on the cutter head allows the use of up to 3 pairs of blades which can easily handle most cutting, stripping and slitting requirements.

 

Automatic Inline Cable Processing

There are various accessories available for all PowerStrip 9500 models. From basic pre- and postprocessing equipment to high-end solutions for fully integrated inline processing, Schleuniger offers the right match for your production needs.

Ulmer ALSeries

 

The delivery trays of the AL series are automatic, electro-pnaumatic delivery systems, which work in line with cutting and stripping machines. Is it possible to deliver material up to 12mm diameter and a minimum length of 500mm. A constant running transport belt pulls the material into the device. A sensor system on the infeed nozzle recognises the end of material and starts the output action. The pneumatically moved delivery tunnel puts the material into the tub.
Material with over length can also be delivered because of the open end of the delivery tunnel.

As an option the delivery tray can be equipped with an intermediate tray, which allows the delivery of material bundles.

All crimp terminals are supplied with paper linings.

Crimp terminals, end sleeves and cable eyelets are used for solderless cable connections:

End sleeves are standardized in accordance with DIN 46228 part 1 – 4. They are used to prevent individual wires of stranded conductors from fraying, e.g. when mounted to a terminal block. Insulated end sleeves have a plastic flange to prevent the conductor being touched.


Ring terminals and cable eyelets are suitable for direct contacting of a cable with a screw.

Tabs and receptacles are standardized in accordance with DIN 46247 part 1 – 3, DIN 46343 and DIN 46346, and are used – just as round plug pins and bushings – for detachable plug connections.

All parts listed comply to EC directives 2000/53/EC (end-of-life vehicles),

2002/95/EC (ROHS), and 2003/11/EC, and are supplied in accordance with the requirements of DIN ISO 9001:2000.

Pneumatic Stripping Machine

The UniStrip 2545 is a pneumatic wire and cable stripping machine specifically designed for jacket stripping of Glass Fiber Optic (GOF) cables and discrete wires up to 3.2 mm (0.12'') O.D.. At a wire size range of 0.03 - 2.08 mm² (AWG 14 - 32), the compact machine strips lengths from 25 up to 45 mm (1" - 1.8'').

A Simple Solution

Extremely short cycle times and easily adjustable stripping lengths and diameters boost productivity when building cable assemblies and other quick-change wire jobs. The versatility and precision of this semi-automatic stripper ensures productivity in a wide variety of applications. The UniStrip 2545 is a light, but nevertheless very precise machine and strips most insulation types with just one set of blades for greater efficiency.

Operating the UniStrip 2545 is extremely simple. After insertion, the cable makes contact with the sensor, which then actuates the visual controllable stripping process.

Ulmer SAR600

The coil unwinder SAR600 has been designed as a strain free cable feeder. The bigger unwinders are the SAR800/1000/1250. The spool is driven by two rollers on the outside diameter of the spool flange. The main driver is a frequency controlled three-phases-motor. The coil unwinder is regulated by the sag control DHS1000 or alternatively with dancer arm.

The system guaranteed that the product is feed to the processing machine without any pull in the opposite direction. The concept eliminates the undesirable stretching of the isolation of cables.

Ulmer ZG 15 S

The feeder ZG15 S is driven by an electronically controlled DC-motor. It is continuously adjustable with two potentiometers. 

 The speed is set at the “Feed” potentiometers. The final speed depends on this value. Final speed = set speed + regulator arm. During operation, the regulator arm is lifted by the material fed and the feeder accelerates to the new set value. When the downstream processing machine stops running, the regulator arm lowers and ZG15S reduces its speed.

SAG Control DHS 1000 D

The sag control DHS1000 is a fully electronic loop control which is able to recognise very thin materials using optical sensors. Five sensors enable smooth control of speed over an output potential of 0-10 volts. Using five potentiometers it is possible to set the level of the set value.

The distance between the sensors and the reflectors is ca. 100 mm. Our test procedures show that even a transparent tube of 3 mm diameter is readily recognised.

The DHS1000 controls our feeders types ZG200 B2 or ZG15 S also with the cutting machine SM15, with our De-Reeler ARG30 M and SAR 600/800/1000/1250. The sag control can be used for extrusion processing.

Ulmer ZG200 B2

The feeder ZG200 B2 is designed to feed materials such cables, hoses, tapes, flat cable, and the like to cutting and stripping machines, cutters and punching presses.

 

It is driven by an electronically controlled direct current motor, which is continuously adjustable with two potentiometers.

One potentiometer sets the feed speed and the other is set by a control lever touching the material fed. Additionally the feed speed can be controlled by a contact-free sag control DHS1000.

The material is fed by two synchronized 50 mm wide toothed belts. Both belts are coated with an abrasion-protection. The distance between the aces of the feeder belt wheels is 200 mm. The throughput height is adjustable between 0 and 30 mm. The feed belt mechanism may either be furnished with adjustable upper belt or parallel adjustment of both belts. The belt lifting is air-operated is manually operated with a hand wheel and throughput height indicator. On both feed and output end, the material is feed through nozzles. This prevents operators from being injured by reaching into the machine. The unit conforms to CE regulations.

Schleuniger OS9450 OmniStrip

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

Automatic Cut & Strip Machine

The OmiStrip 9450 automatic cut & strip machine precisely processes wires and cables with cross-sections up to 16 mm² (AWG 6) and diameters up to 11 mm (0.43"). Its wide application range and the outstanding price/performance ratio make the OmniStrip 9450 an ideal solution for medium to low volume wire processing demands.

With simultaneously running processes, short cycle times and fast change-overs between jobs, the belt-driven OmniStrip 9450 ensures a high output rate. Multiple processing tasks can be carried out in a single step thanks to the high dynamic Schleuniger indexing cutter head and userfriendly programming.

Programming Made Easy

The intuitive programming can be done either in simple mode or library mode. A clearly laid out display shows all important information. Libraries for raw materials and processing parameters have been integrated allowing a new kind of easy and time saving programming: For a cable, simply choose a raw material and a processing. The various processing steps are automatically determined by pre-defined cable ends.

Processing parameters only have to be programmed once. When changing a parameter (e.g. incision depth) this is allocated to all cables using the same processing parameters - with one command only. Long text strings (e.g. inkjet text strings) can be entered comfortably via USB keyboard.

To make programming even easier, Cayman PC software can be used with OmniStrip 9450. This optional wire processing software allows the programming of the entire production line via your PC. Cayman offers time saving solutions to cable entries and gives you a big advantage in managing your wire lists.

Get Connected!

As a standard, the OmniStrip 9450 features an integrated Pre-/ Post Feed Interface (PPI) allowing flexible control and monitoring of a wide range of peripherals and even complex customer specific devices. Cables can be marked simultaneously with inkjet and hotstamp. The inkjet protocols for select inkjet printer models (e.g. Metronic alphaJET C) are included in the scope of delivery.

Programming of the synchronization signals, control and monitoring of all devices can be done easily via panel of the OmniStrip 9450. The OmniStrip 9450 may be used as a stand-alone machine as well as an integral componant of a complete processing line.

Ulmer SM15 2P

The universal cutting machines of the SM series facilitate an effective production of different materials and are characterized by their compact size and user friendly handling.

The machines are used to cut hoses, cables, braid, ropes, foils and similar materials in the serial production of the automotive, electronic and plastics industries.

Because of the multiline infeed entry and the synchronized belt drive, the correct material position to the cutting blade is guaranteed.

With a various option program the devices can be equipped on customers demands.

All cutting machines of the SM series can be combined and extended with other devices from our house.

The transport belts of the SM15 2P are driven by an 250Watt DC-motor with a clutch-brake-combination. The adjustment of material material length and pieces are set by the operator on the two electro-mechanical counters. The speed adjustment works with a potentiometer. All control panels are in a good available position.

Schleuniger CS5300NT

The CoaxStrip 5300 NT is a fully programmable multi-step stripping machine for micro-coaxial, coaxial, triaxial, multi-conductor cable and single conductor wire. This benchtop unit can easily process cables with inner conductors ranging from 0.15 mm (AWG 36) up to 4 mm (0.157'') maximum cable outer diameter and strips lengths up to 27 mm (1.06").

 

The high-precision CoaxStrip 5300 NT excels with short cycle times and high productivity. Due to its open construction and an air-jet cleaning the blades and the centering jaws, the stripping head requires little maintenance.

New Stripping Head Design

 
Sophisticated centering and incision mechanics allow high precision processing of cables that are difficult to handle such asmicro-coxial cables, cables with soft insulation, or dielectric materials. The new stripping head design allows the blades to travel perpendicular to the cable axis. This results in consistently superior stripping quality and longer blade life. The high rotary speed of the stripping head, programmable blade feed rate and improved cutting concept guarantee high precision incisions into the individual layers of a multi-layer cable without damaging adjacent layers.
 
Rotating cable centralizers are mounted directly in front of the blades. The CoaxStrip 5300 NT comes with universal V-type centralizers as standard. Cable-specific radius type centralizers are also available for processing thin cable diameters. These custom-madecentralizers are made a few hundredths of a millimeter larger than the cable; therefore no torque is applied to the cable. This enables precise incisions without twisting the cable.
 
High Performance & User-Friendliness
 
Short cycle times and wire list processing ensure high performance and will yield you a quick return on investment. To guarantee short operator training times, the CoaxStrip 5300 NT can be programmed intuitively with a Graphical User Interface (GUI).
 

Its high-resolution monochrome display allows the user to view a schematic diagram of the cable end, complete with programmed dimensions. Using Iguana all data can be backed up conveniently on a regular PC.

Pneumatic Stripping Machine

The UniStrip 2015 is a pneumatic wire and cable stripping machine and the perfect solution for stripping discrete wires and small multi-conductor cables up to 3.2 mm (0.12") O.D.. The compact machine strips lengths up to 20 mm (0.78").

UniStrip 2015 machines prove themselves each day in countless industrial plants around the world. Extremely short cycle times and infinite settings for conductor diameters, stripping and pull-off lengths boost productivity immensely when building harnesses or other quick-change wire stripping applications.

The UniStrip 2015 is a highly portable machine and strips most insulation types with just one set of blades for greater efficiency.

A Simple Way to Extremely Short Wires & Cables

Operating the UniStrip 2015 is extremely simple. After insertion, the cable makes contact with the sensor, which then actuates the visual controllable stripping process.

Due to the minimal distance between the acryl safety cover and the stripping blades, the UniStrip 2015 can perform stripping on extremely short wires and cables.

SUHR SC430 USP

 

 

Heat Sealing Machines
Type SC430 USP
The above machine is a microprocessor controlled cutting machine designed and manufactured in Denmark. It measures and cuts almost any type of synthetic strip material from thin ribbons to heavy webbings with an electrically heated, compressed air driven knife. An extractor fan is built into the machine for exhausting the fumes generated by the melting material.

The machine can measure and cut small or large quantities of strip materials up to125mm wide, in length from 1mm to 99.9 metres and produce consistently accurate lengths and high quality cuts. Frequently used lengths can be stored in the machines memory for instant recall. There are eight memories available for this purpose.

The machine is portable and weighs approximately 20Kg. It can be mounted on a table or bench and requires only 230V/50Hz mains socket and a clean, dry compressed air supply.

Schleuniger CS5500

 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

Programmable Coaxial Stripping Machine

The CoaxStrip 5500 is a semi-automatic, programmable stripping machine designed to perform both single and multiple stage strips. Its processing capabilities make the CoaxStrip 5500 a perfect match for a wide range of wires and cables such as coaxial and multi-conductor cables - even with very thin and tough or slightly out-of-round insulations - with a maximum outside diameter of 15 mm (0.59'') at a maximum stripping length of 85 mm (3.35").

Precision mechanics, combined with state-of-the-art electronics, a user-friendly display and included PC software create an easy to use platform which offers maximum efficiency. This machine is ideal for low volume, quick changeover applications as well as high volume production runs, giving the best possible flexibility and productivity to your production methods.

 

A Worthy Successor to the MP 8015

The CoaxStrip 5500 is the new generation coaxial cable stripping machine replacing the MP 8015. Improved handling with a large graphical display, increased program capacity and additional features combined with proven precision mechanics make the CoaxStrip 5500 a worthy successor to this legendary machine.

 

Unmatched precision

The unique stripping head design combines universal stripping blades with a universal centering system. This allows the CoaxStrip 5500 to process the entire range of cable types and diameters with no blade change whatsoever. The patented stripping head is precision-built to guarantee unparalleled stripping quality and repeatable results.

 

High Precision and User Friendliness

Short cycle times and wire list processing ensure high performance and will yield you a quick return on investment. To guarantee short operator training times, the CoaxStrip 5500 can be programmed intuitively with a Graphical User Interface (GUI).
Its high-resolution monochrome display allows the user to view a schematic diagram of the cable end, complete with programmed dimensions.

 

The Schleuniger design approach to combine high precision, high performance and user-friendliness in all our machines, has been fully incorporated into the CoaxStrip 5500. If you already have other new generation Schleuniger machines, you and your operators will find it very convenient that software handling of the machines always follows the same principle. In other words - if you know how to use one Schleuniger machine, you know how to use other Schleuniger machines as well.

Schleuniger Uni Strip 2300
 Click to view the Product Brochure

 

UniStrip 2300


Application Range / Function


The Schleuniger UniStrip 2300 strips wires ranging in size from 0.03 – 6 mm2 (32 –

10 AWG) and jacketed cables up to 5.5 mm (0.22“) in diameter. This innovative machine

does not require any mechanical adjustments to process different wire sizes.

Using the color touchscreen, the operator selects the desired wire size from the preprogrammed

library and all parameters (cutting diameter, clamping pressure, blade

way back, etc.) are automatically set. The operator edits the stripping and pull-off

lengths as required and the machine is ready for operation. The UniStrip 2300 begins

the stripping process when the wire end touches the trigger sensor. The wire is automatically

clamped and the stripping process is performed according to the programmed

values. If desired, the program can be saved to internal memory for future

use.

 

Special Features

􀂃 Intuitive color touch screen user interface

􀂃 Can strip inner conductors of jacketed cables with short break out lengths

􀂃 No mechanical adjustments required when changing wire sizes

􀂃 Very sensitive trigger sensor – works great for small, flexible wires

􀂃 Operator has clear view of the entire working area


Programmable Processing Parameters
 

􀂃 Cutting diameter, cutting speed

􀂃 Blade way back (default values in “Basic Wire”, programmable in “Extended

Wire”)


􀂃 Stripping length, pull-off length, pull-off speed

􀂃 Trimming function (for precise strip lengths)

􀂃 Cable clamping pressure

products_description:
Schleuniger StripCrimp 200

 

 Click to view the Product Brochure
 

 

Get to know one of the most flexible stripper crimper machines: The fully programmable StripCrimp 200. This machine is most suitable for high precision stripping and subsequent crimping of side- or rear-feed terminals for wires between 30 - 12 AWG (0.05 – 4.00 mm²). The strip and crimp machine StripCrimp 200 captivates by great flexibility and user-friendly operation. The machine is highly suitable as a semi-automatic stripper crimper or within fully automatic transfer systems and runs fast, quietly and safely.

Flexibility and User-friendliness

All stripping parameters and special functions are programmable through a user-friendly operating panel. All relevant parameters are displayed on the multi-lingual display

The user is guided through the intuitive menus so the parameters for a wide range of applications can be entered easily and efficiently. Furthermore, the menu structure helps to minimize entry errors and maximize productivity. The StripCrimp 200 includes a program memory for all stripping parameters. Finally, all stripping slugs are removed by a suction device and discarded through the side of the machine.

Thanks to the quick-change base plate applicators are changed in seconds. Crimp height can be easily adjusted on the press with the standard fine-adjust (micro-adjust) mechanism. Wayback and recut are additional functions which can be enabled software-wise and therefore make the unit even more versatile.

Sumake B412L

 

High performance brushless motor design for increased durability and flexibility
 

This is a brand new electric screwdriver range from Sumake featuring a new brushless motor. The benefits of this new motor design are to improve durability and offer a wider range of torque and r.p.m - this is because in brushless motors commutation is achieved electronically and therefore they are capable of very high speeds and torque without arcing.
 

As brushless motors have a lower thermal resistance they are able to operate in a much wider temperature range and will achieve a higher duty cycle.  No brushes also mean a reduction in maintenance and no brush contamination to the bearing or environment which also makes this screwdriver safer when in contact with fluids due to the elimination of arcing.


Lastly due to the lower thermal resistance, these drivers are capable of operating in wider temperature ranges, have higher torque to inertia ratios, and greater acceleration.  The smaller brushless motor can do the same job as their much larger counterparts would otherwise be used for - this also results in a reduction in costs.

Other Options

 

In addition to the standard range of brushless screwdrivers and also the range with built in counter, we can also offer the option of a special power supply which also functions as a screw counter - SP-BC32HL60T/C.  This requires a dedicated screwdriver which is the "BC " range (SUEA-BC203L through to SUEA-BC419L).
 



Compatible with PLC based process control system, this offers accurate counting on screw fastening and the ability to set running speed and timing by the inbuilt slow start function. Other features include the selection of either auto-reset retrieval or manual reset retrieval, displaying the number of unfinished screw counts - the user can add an external sensor switch to prevent operation error, buzzer alert when completing a fastening cycle, built in auto leaning function - which could judge the best setting value. The Power supply enhances the auto-identified screw fastening time mode - allowing the user to aim at simulating the duration of specific screw fastening.


Through stringent manufacturers trials we are confident to state that these screwdrivers are an equivalent quality to HIOS and Delvo and offer a much more competitive price.

Automatic Cut & Strip Machine


The powerful EcoStrip 9320 processes round cables up to 9 mm (0.35") O.D. and flat ribbon cables up to 13 mm (0.51") width with pull-off lengths up to 100 mm (3.94") on the right end (leading end) and 45 mm (1.77'') on the left end (trailing end).

Business Class at Economy Rate

At the push of a button, the cable is automatically loaded and its diameter determined. Based on this value, the transport belts then automatically adjust which avoids overstressing the transport units. Another very useful feature is the universal wire guide block which integrates all possible standard wire guides in just one tool.

According to your production needs, a choice of stripping blades for various types of cables and flat ribbon cables are available allowing multiple processing for a higher production output.

Automatic Inline Cable Processing

By combining an EcoStrip 9320 (3) with a Schleuniger prefeeding machine (1) and a hotstamp or inkjet marking machine (2), a complete production line can be established. Various models are available for feeding, marking, stacking and coiling of wire and cable.

Loepfe RM100 Cable Marking


 

Application

The RM100 is used for circumferential markings of cables wires, or cords using the proven hot stamping process. Foil coated on one side with printing substance is pressed onto the material with a hot stamp. Through pressure and heat the stamp is marked onto the material. In order to obtain a circumferential marking, two half-shells are used. 

Later, the marking can be used as installation help, positioning, identification, dividing position etc. 

The RM100 can be used as single unit with a foot pedal or together with an upstream machine. In addition, the Ringmarker and the control unit can be installed separately.

The UniStrip 2500 is a pneumatic wire and cable stripping machine and the perfect solution for stripping discrete wires and small multi-conductor cables up to 6 mm (0.24") O.D..

The compact machine strips lengths up to 30 mm (1.18") and comes standard with V-blades, the optimum solution for any ordinary stripping of stranded wire with no blade changeover necessary.

A Simple Solution for Versatile Cable Processing

Through the use of special blades, the range of applications can be expanded to include flat ribbon cable, double-stranded wire, thin multi-stranded wire or demanding (tough, delicate, thin) isolations. The adjustable wayback prevents the conductor from being damaged during the stripping process.

UniStrip 2500 machines prove themselves each day in countless industrial plants around the world. Extremely short cycle times and infinite settings for conductor diameters, stripping and pull-off lengths boost productivity immensely when building harnesses or other quick-change wire stripping applications.

Operating the US 2500 is extremely simple. After insertion, the cable makes contact with the sensor, which then actuates the visually controllable stripping process. Alternatively a foot pedal is available as an option.

Take the product tour for additional information such as wire & cable samples, processing capabilities overview and technical specifications.

The PreFeeder 2500 is an active dereeler and the ideal feeding system for wire, small cables and tubing. It is a simple solution for large production output and offers an excellent price / performance ratio.

The feeding process allows rapid acceleration of the motorized reel while maintaining low forces on the material being fed - a prerequisite for precision processing with short cycle times. Simple operation and easy handling when changing spools provide for short change-over times.

Choose Between Different Versions

The PreFeeder 2500 is available in a 40 kg or 80 kg (88 or 177 lbs.) version, based on maximum reel weight.

Depending on your production needs, the PreFeeder 2500 can either be fitted with an integrated accumulator or be deployed with an external sag control PreFeederControl 2

Powerful and Absolutely Reliable

The dynamic PreFeeder 3500, a cable feeding system within the Schleuniger assortment, is powerful, competitive, user-friendly and space-saving.

All axes required are electric driven. As of its special clamping and power system no shaft - axes and additional carriers are needed. For high dynamic, the integrated cable accumulator is optimally adjusted with the dereeling drive. Surveillance functions provide greater security during setup and operation. 
Despite the small dimensioned housing, it can take spools with a diameter of 400 – 920 mm (15.75" - 36.2") and 315 – 712 mm (12.4" - 28") width. The cable accumulator is integrated as a set up onto the deleerer housing. It functions according to the dancer arm principle.


User-Friendly & Simple Operation Concept

The operating elements are clearly arranged and logical in their use. The simple operation concept with motorized axes allows spool handling by one person. Thanks to the spool lift even 300 kg (661 lbs.) spools can be aligned with minimal effort. The ergonomically arranged rolls of the cable accumulator allow a quick cable loading. The spools are electrically lifted at the push of a button.

The active deleerer is loaded from the front side to save space.

The PreFeeder 3500 is built according to CE standards. Additional safety functions automatically control the operation and efficient functioning of the processing line.

With the PreFeeder 3500 you will decisively enhance your processing line. Thanks to consistent concentration on essential functions, its cost effective design and high achieved productivity, the acquisition of a PreFeeder 3500 fits any investment list without putting a strain on the budget. Furthermore, compact design contributes to a small footprint.

Prefeeding Machine Puller Type

The highly dynamic PreFeeder 60 prefeeding machine has been specially designed for use with fully automatic crimping machines such as the Schleuniger CrimpCenter models. It feeds wire and cable up to 6 mm² (9 AWG).

High Dynamic and Yet Gentle

A controlled roller drive feeds the wire into the accumulator from where it is pulled by the processing machine for further processing. This high dynamic system ensures gentle and continuous feeding at highest speed, even when using difficult to feed cable bundles (e.g. wire barrels, loose wires, cardboard boxes or Conipack).

With a maximum feeding rate of 9 m/s (29.53 ft./s) - depending on wire type and bundle, the PreFeeder 60 is an excellent solution to keep the production rate of the processing machine at a high level. Further features are height-adjustable feet and - as an option - a sensor for wire end detection.

To load the de-reeler the drum flyer is placed uprightly by 90°.

After removing the bottom protection plate it is possible to move the drum on the front side onto the shaft by using a jack lift.

After placing the de-reeling unit back into horizontal position and after clipping on the flyer, the de-reeling unit is ready for operation within a few minutes.

Now the cable is decoiled by the flyer rotating about the drum and is pulled off via the discharging tube installed above.

The EC 65 is compact and lightweight, yet rugged enough for the factory floor. It is well suited for complex cable harness assemblies.

The EC 65 is an ideal device to securely crimp wires and cable terminals such as:    

 

  • Insulated cable lugs to 6 mm 2 / 10 AWG   

  • Tubular cable lugs, solderless terminals to 10 mm 2 / 8 AWG   

  • Flat tab terminals to 6 mm 2 / 10 AWG   

  • Wire end sleeves to 50 mm 2 / 1 AWG       
      

The EC 65 can be operated in one of two modes.

   
    Mode 1: controls the entire crimp process by pressing down the pedal switch.   

   
    Mode 2: allows the user to fix the terminal on the cable by actuating the foot switch once. To finish the crimping process, he presses down the foot switch once again. Mode 2 is used for more complex terminals.

   
The onset of compression force can be adjusted for each new terminal to satisfy crimp integrity. That way, damage to dies and terminals can be minimised.    
   
Simply press a button to select the opening for each die.    
   
Since some female terminals are more difficult to crimp, a moveable locator can be utilised to ensure proper crimping.    
   
Various standard dies are available, as well as dies designed to customer specifications.    
   
Accessories: Locator for crimping female disconnects / Its carrying handle converts the EC 65 into a portable crimping tool.
